b"Tomorrow is the International Day of Peace \xe2\x80\x93 a day set aside by the United Nations to focus the world on peace and generate awareness for the need to eradicate war and violence. 

To mark the day, McDonald's along with DreamWorks Animation, Google, Facebook, Twitter, Cargill, McCain Foods, MasterCard, Burger King and United Airlines have joined to support the U.N.\xe2\x80\x99s World Food Programme and raise awareness and some much needed funding to fight hunger. Unfortunately, the need for help is growing every day. Right now, 60 million refugees have been forced from their homes as a result of war and conflict, more people than at any time since World War II. In just the past few weeks, the world has seen hundreds of thousands more people displaced. Half of the refugees are children\xe2\x80\xa6and all of them struggle daily with hunger.

The ad we\xe2\x80\x99ve created and its message about war and hunger will be shared on television and in digital placements in nearly 40 countries around the globe as we invite people to donate to the World Food Programme. I hope you\xe2\x80\x99ll share it with your friends and make a needed contribution so that those displaced can get the help they desperately need.  
 
You can watch the ad below or here http://McD.to/peaceday
 
Thank you, Steve - McDonald's CEO"

b'Our friend & McDonald\xe2\x80\x99s pioneer, Fred Turner, passed away last night.  Fred is credited by many as the co-founder of McDonald\xe2\x80\x99s Corporation, alongside founder Ray Kroc. He was hired by Ray in 1956 as a grill man at Kroc\xe2\x80\x99s first McDonald\xe2\x80\x99s restaurant in Des Plaines, IL.

Fred was the mastermind behind such innovations as Chicken McNuggets & Hamburger University. McDonald\xe2\x80\x99s wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t have been the same without him. 

During tenure as President/CEO, Turner grew our system from 1,000 to more than 9,500 restaurants worldwide.

Fred Turner worked for McDonald\xe2\x80\x99s for 48 years (1956-2004). He remained active as McDonald\xe2\x80\x99s Honorary Chairman of the Board until his passing. 

http://www.aboutmcdonalds.com/mcd/newsroom/image_and_video_library/fred_turner.html'
